-- Telefonica Czech Shareholders Approved $2.1 a Share Dividend
-- B y   L e n k a   P o n i k e l s k a
-- 2012-04-19T15:10:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-19/telefonica-czech-shareholders-approved-dividend-from-2011-profit.html
Telefonica Czech Republic AS (SPTT) 
shareholders approved a dividend payout of 40 koruna ($2.1) a
share, of which 13 koruna represents a share-capital reduction,
company spokesman Hany Farghali said in an e-mail today.  The shareholders also approved today a potential share
buyback of as much as 10 percent of the company’s shares,
Farghali said.  Prague-based Telefonica Czech, the country largest phone
operator, is controlled by Spain’s  Telefonica SA. (TEF)   To contact the reporter on this story:
Lenka Ponikelska in Prague at 
 lponikelska1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
